1
00:01:04,682 --> 00:01:08,978
MAD CONCRETE DREAMS

2
00:01:14,937 --> 00:01:16,772
10 YEARS AGO

3
00:01:16,855 --> 00:01:19,191
MIN HWAL-SUNG & JEON YI-GYEONG
WE WISH YOU A HAPPY MARRIAGE

4
00:01:23,237 --> 00:01:26,156
We have Da-rae here.
Do we have to be at the after-party?

5
00:01:26,615 --> 00:01:28,617
We can't skip it.
It's Hwal-sung's wedding.

6
00:01:28,701 --> 00:01:30,369
I was the MC for the ceremony

7
00:01:30,452 --> 00:01:31,870
and he also got me a golf bag.

8
00:01:33,205 --> 00:01:34,248
Da-rae.

9
00:01:34,331 --> 00:01:35,624
Have a fishcake.

10
00:01:35,708 --> 00:01:37,126
Fishcake.

11
00:01:39,628 --> 00:01:41,213
Gi Su-jong. Long time no see.

12
00:01:41,463 --> 00:01:42,965
Jung Man-sik, you're here as well?

13
00:01:43,048 --> 00:01:44,091
I should be here.

14
00:01:44,842 --> 00:01:46,552
- It's been a while, Seon.
- Yes, hi.

15
00:01:46,844 --> 00:01:47,886
You punk.

16
00:01:48,220 --> 00:01:49,722
You haven't changed at all.

17
00:01:49,805 --> 00:01:50,806
I haven't.

18
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:54,393
So you must be...

19
00:01:54,476 --> 00:01:55,728
What's your name?

20
00:01:57,146 --> 00:01:59,064
It's Da-rae. Gi Da-rae.

21
00:02:00,482 --> 00:02:02,901
Da-rae, say hello.

22
00:02:04,445 --> 00:02:09,074
(Hello, I am Gi Da-rae.)

23
00:02:10,743 --> 00:02:13,120
- You're really quite pretty.
- Hey.

24
00:02:13,203 --> 00:02:14,413
You don't have to shout.

25
00:02:14,496 --> 00:02:15,831
She can read your lips.

26
00:02:16,624 --> 00:02:18,626
Oh, really? Then...

27
00:02:18,709 --> 00:02:20,127
Will you pour me a shot... No.

28
00:02:21,378 --> 00:02:22,671
Will you pour me some soda?

29
00:02:34,058 --> 00:02:35,476
Would you like some, too?

30
00:02:37,770 --> 00:02:39,104
She can't drink anything sweet.

31
00:02:40,272 --> 00:02:41,440
No, she can't.

32
00:02:41,523 --> 00:02:42,650
Da-rae.

33
00:02:44,026 --> 00:02:45,110
Let's drink.

34
00:02:46,403 --> 00:02:47,404
Cheers.

35
00:02:51,367 --> 00:02:52,368
They're here!

36
00:03:00,459 --> 00:03:02,002
Congratulations!

37
00:03:03,253 --> 00:03:04,546
You look great!

38
00:03:07,841 --> 00:03:11,261
I'm almost the last of us to marry,
so I'll keep it short.

39
00:03:13,514 --> 00:03:15,599
I told you not to marry too soon.

40
00:03:16,141 --> 00:03:17,935
- What's he saying?
- Come on.

41
00:03:18,227 --> 00:03:21,146
The last one to smile
is the true victor.

42
00:03:21,438 --> 00:03:23,440
Come on, man.

43
00:03:23,941 --> 00:03:26,068
Gosh, Min Hwal-sung.

44
00:03:26,151 --> 00:03:27,986
Thank you for the jeers.

45
00:03:28,612 --> 00:03:30,989
I'd like to thank you all for coming.

46
00:03:32,574 --> 00:03:35,828
There's one thing I really must say.

47
00:03:37,579 --> 00:03:40,416
My best friend Su-jong.

48
00:03:43,127 --> 00:03:44,253
Stand up.

49
00:03:53,470 --> 00:03:55,139
I wouldn't be here if not for you.

50
00:03:56,724 --> 00:03:58,559
Thanks for hosting the ceremony.

51
00:04:01,770 --> 00:04:03,063
- Are you okay?
- Darn it.

52
00:04:09,153 --> 00:04:10,571
May our friendship last forever.

53
00:04:13,741 --> 00:04:15,200
- Congratulations.
- Thanks.

54
00:04:16,744 --> 00:04:18,245
Congratulations, Yi-gyeong.

55
00:04:19,621 --> 00:04:22,291
To my friend Su-jong, his wife

56
00:04:22,374 --> 00:04:23,876
and his daughter Da-rae.

57
00:04:25,043 --> 00:04:26,128
I dedicate this song.

58
00:04:33,385 --> 00:04:35,679
<i>Eight, two, seven, eight, nine.</i>

59
00:04:38,807 --> 00:04:40,058
<i>SHAKY FRIENDSHIP</i>

60
00:04:50,778 --> 00:04:51,779
Clap.

61
00:05:07,836 --> 00:05:09,505
<i>I know it's wrong</i>

62
00:05:09,588 --> 00:05:13,884
<i>So why do I have feelings</i>
<i>For my friend's girl?</i>

63
00:05:14,301 --> 00:05:16,720
<i>I tell myself I must stop</i>

64
00:05:16,804 --> 00:05:21,600
<i>So why do thoughts of her</i>
<i>Fill my mind?</i>

65
00:05:21,683 --> 00:05:24,686
<i>She called me without telling her man</i>

66
00:05:24,770 --> 00:05:28,190
<i>Why does that make me feel so good?</i>

67
00:05:28,273 --> 00:05:31,276
<i>I could be cool and just reject her</i>

68
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:34,363
<i>So why can't I seem to do that?</i>

69
00:05:34,696 --> 00:05:38,575
<i>It's driving me crazy</i>

70
00:05:38,659 --> 00:05:42,079
<i>I don't know what got into me</i>

71
00:05:42,162 --> 00:05:45,582
<i>I'm ignoring</i>
<i>A long-standing friendship</i>

72
00:05:45,666 --> 00:05:48,627
<i>Because I'm falling for a girl</i>

73
00:05:48,710 --> 00:05:52,381
<i>It's torture, pure torment</i>

74
00:05:52,464 --> 00:05:56,009
<i>It would be fine</i>
<i>If I could just give up</i>

75
00:05:56,093 --> 00:06:00,097
<i>Why am I putting so much thought</i>

76
00:06:00,180 --> 00:06:02,641
<i>Into something so pointless?</i>
All together.

77
00:06:02,724 --> 00:06:06,311
<i>I'm sorry, dear friend</i>

78
00:06:06,395 --> 00:06:09,857
<i>I deceived you for a while</i>

79
00:06:09,940 --> 00:06:13,819
<i>The friendship I had with you so far</i>

80
00:06:13,902 --> 00:06:16,488
<i>Must not be strong enough</i>

81
00:06:16,572 --> 00:06:20,325
<i>I hope you understand, dear friend</i>

82
00:06:20,409 --> 00:06:23,829
<i>Our friendship was shaky for a while</i>

83
00:06:23,912 --> 00:06:30,419
<i>Pretend someone got jealous</i>
<i>Of what we had</i>

84
00:06:30,502 --> 00:06:36,383
<i>And decided to test us</i>

85
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:52,441
MAD CONCRETE DREAMS

86
00:06:53,483 --> 00:06:55,819
EPISODE 7

87
00:06:58,864 --> 00:07:00,532
Well? Do you like it?

88
00:07:01,116 --> 00:07:03,327
Do I even have to answer?

89
00:07:04,953 --> 00:07:07,789
What are we doing here?

90
00:07:08,248 --> 00:07:09,249
Seon.

91
00:07:09,958 --> 00:07:11,209
Give me three years.

92
00:07:11,627 --> 00:07:13,170
I'll buy this apartment

93
00:07:13,253 --> 00:07:14,379
and put it in your name.

94
00:07:30,270 --> 00:07:32,481
- Did you look around?
- Yes.

95
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:35,317
- Isn't it nice?
- It's lovely.

96
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:37,945
Mr. Gi, just buy it already.

97
00:07:39,112 --> 00:07:41,323
- I should.
- Come over here.

98
00:07:41,406 --> 00:07:44,409
This is the only apartment
of this size with this view.

99
00:07:46,495 --> 00:07:48,997
- It's great.
- Right? You can see right across.

100
00:07:49,081 --> 00:07:50,874
And there's easy access
to public transport.

101
00:08:01,885 --> 00:08:04,471
What's going on? Is Da-rae not home?

102
00:08:04,805 --> 00:08:07,975
Oh, she said she'd watch a movie
with some friends.

103
00:08:08,684 --> 00:08:10,310
- You shower first.
- Okay.

104
00:08:11,353 --> 00:08:12,354
Seon.

105
00:08:12,896 --> 00:08:14,106
Let's shower together.

106
00:08:16,858 --> 00:08:17,859
What?

107
00:08:18,610 --> 00:08:19,611
Well...

108
00:08:21,238 --> 00:08:23,657
It's been a while. How about...

109
00:08:27,285 --> 00:08:28,286
we do it?

110
00:08:41,008 --> 00:08:42,134
You're home.

111
00:08:43,552 --> 00:08:44,553
Hi, Da-rae.

112
00:08:45,804 --> 00:08:46,805
You go ahead

113
00:08:47,848 --> 00:08:48,849
and shower.

114
00:08:50,350 --> 00:08:51,435
Go shower.

115
00:09:06,074 --> 00:09:08,827
FOR LEASE
CONTACT M&A REALTORS

116
00:09:11,038 --> 00:09:12,956
DEPUTY NAM SANG-HO

117
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:14,124
<i>Great work.</i>

118
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:16,460
<i>I knew I had an eye for people.</i>

119
00:09:18,795 --> 00:09:20,547
<i>I'll do even better in the future.</i>

120
00:09:37,105 --> 00:09:38,106
Hey.

121
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:44,946
Are you happy?

122
00:09:50,285 --> 00:09:51,286
Hey, Hwal-sung.

123
00:09:52,162 --> 00:09:53,205
What's going on?

124
00:09:57,167 --> 00:09:58,168
Su-jong.

125
00:09:58,585 --> 00:10:01,046
You ride this indoors
and bike outdoors.

126
00:10:01,296 --> 00:10:02,839
Are you a professional cyclist?

127
00:10:03,757 --> 00:10:06,510
Forget that. What happened?
How did you leave the hospital?

128
00:10:06,802 --> 00:10:08,136
How would I know?

129
00:10:09,846 --> 00:10:11,932
My eyes just snapped open.

130
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:16,353
Do you know the first person
who came to mind?

131
00:10:20,232 --> 00:10:21,650
It was you.

132
00:10:21,942 --> 00:10:24,444
It wasn't Yi-gyeong or my mom.

133
00:10:24,528 --> 00:10:25,612
You.

134
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:32,202
So Yi-gyeong's mom died like that

135
00:10:32,577 --> 00:10:35,539
and the first-floor café owner
took the fall for it all?

136
00:10:36,998 --> 00:10:38,750
And Seon is clueless?

137
00:10:39,459 --> 00:10:41,002
She doesn't know anything.

138
00:10:41,253 --> 00:10:44,297
You colluded with Deputy Nam
to buy Mr. Kim's property?

139
00:10:44,548 --> 00:10:45,549
Yes.

140
00:10:45,632 --> 00:10:46,967
That Deputy Nam punk.

141
00:10:47,968 --> 00:10:49,344
I heard bad things about him.

142
00:10:50,095 --> 00:10:51,972
I should've been there to advise you.

143
00:10:52,055 --> 00:10:54,182
Yi-gyeong helped a great deal.

144
00:10:54,474 --> 00:10:55,475
Yi-gyeong?

145
00:10:59,229 --> 00:11:00,772
Okay, where's my share?

146
00:11:02,107 --> 00:11:04,067
Your share? What's that?

147
00:11:04,901 --> 00:11:06,444
We agreed to split it.

148
00:11:06,528 --> 00:11:09,030
That went out the window
the moment you called the police.

149
00:11:09,114 --> 00:11:10,157
I explained.

150
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,409
I didn't call them.
My mother-in-law did.

151
00:11:12,492 --> 00:11:14,619
You're talking your way out again.

152
00:11:14,703 --> 00:11:16,454
This was your idea.

153
00:11:16,538 --> 00:11:17,789
It's your mess.

154
00:11:18,039 --> 00:11:19,457
You created this whole mess

155
00:11:19,541 --> 00:11:21,418
and I've been through hell
trying to clean it up.

156
00:11:21,668 --> 00:11:22,836
I almost died.

157
00:11:23,086 --> 00:11:24,129
You killed me.

158
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:26,047
You killed me

159
00:11:26,131 --> 00:11:28,341
my mother-in-law, and the café owner.

160
00:11:28,425 --> 00:11:30,343
Are you a serial killer or something?

161
00:11:30,427 --> 00:11:34,890
If that's your excuse,
we can go way back in history.

162
00:11:35,473 --> 00:11:36,683
You're insane.

163
00:11:38,602 --> 00:11:39,603
Hey, Su-jong.

164
00:11:40,645 --> 00:11:42,564
You think I don't know you struggled?

165
00:11:43,190 --> 00:11:45,942
That's why I came here
as soon as I woke up.

166
00:11:46,902 --> 00:11:47,903
All the way here.

167
00:11:47,986 --> 00:11:49,196
Let's do this, then.

168
00:11:49,487 --> 00:11:50,864
We'll call my lawyer

169
00:11:51,531 --> 00:11:53,992
have the contract notarized,
and split the shares.

170
00:11:54,451 --> 00:11:55,619
That's reasonable, isn't it?

171
00:11:57,579 --> 00:11:59,122
I don't have a say in the shares.

172
00:11:59,372 --> 00:12:01,291
It belongs to a corporate body,
not any one person.

173
00:12:02,626 --> 00:12:04,252
- A corporate body?
- Yes.

174
00:12:04,336 --> 00:12:06,421
- Was that Deputy Nam's idea?
- Yes.

175
00:12:06,838 --> 00:12:08,924
Darn it. What the heck?

176
00:12:09,299 --> 00:12:10,759
You stupid loser.

177
00:12:11,092 --> 00:12:13,011
- You can't trust him!
- Hey.

178
00:12:13,428 --> 00:12:16,598
It must belong to a corporation
to be included in the redevelopment.

179
00:12:16,681 --> 00:12:17,933
How much will he give you?

180
00:12:18,016 --> 00:12:19,017
Ten billion won.

181
00:12:20,352 --> 00:12:22,479
What the heck? Hey!

182
00:12:22,729 --> 00:12:25,273
You could get
at least 30 billion out of it!

183
00:12:25,357 --> 00:12:28,109
I don't believe
what this idiot has done.

184
00:12:28,193 --> 00:12:29,194
Hey.

185
00:12:29,527 --> 00:12:31,696
That's why people
take advantage of you.

186
00:12:32,781 --> 00:12:33,865
You frustrating fool.

187
00:12:44,459 --> 00:12:45,460
Yes.

188
00:12:45,710 --> 00:12:47,545
I'm a loser and a doormat.

189
00:12:48,046 --> 00:12:49,673
That's why I get taken advantage of.

190
00:12:50,799 --> 00:12:52,425
I even lost my wife to my friend.

191
00:12:54,552 --> 00:12:55,679
What are you talking about?

192
00:12:55,762 --> 00:12:57,430
- You really don't know?
- What?

193
00:12:58,515 --> 00:12:59,933
You slept with Seon, didn't you?

194
00:13:03,645 --> 00:13:04,646
Sorry, hang on.

195
00:13:07,691 --> 00:13:09,609
All that sudden shouting
gave me a headache.

196
00:13:10,193 --> 00:13:11,528
It's ringing.

197
00:13:12,279 --> 00:13:14,364
- I need to get back to the hospital.
- Wait.

198
00:13:15,031 --> 00:13:16,116
Hwal-sung.

199
00:13:16,449 --> 00:13:17,492
We need to talk.

200
00:13:18,076 --> 00:13:19,327
Learn to brake and take your time.

201
00:13:19,411 --> 00:13:21,079
Why did you sleep with Seon?

202
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:26,334
When did you find out?

203
00:13:26,918 --> 00:13:29,379
You're asking me that right now?

204
00:13:29,963 --> 00:13:30,964
Hey.

205
00:13:31,339 --> 00:13:32,382
Hang on.

206
00:13:33,508 --> 00:13:35,343
Didn't I gift you those clubs?

207
00:13:35,719 --> 00:13:36,803
You did, punk.

208
00:13:38,013 --> 00:13:39,306
Okay.

209
00:13:39,389 --> 00:13:41,266
I'm sorry about Seon.

210
00:13:41,349 --> 00:13:42,892
Do you want me on my knees? I can.

211
00:13:42,976 --> 00:13:45,353
What if Da-rae were to find out?
And Yi-gyeong?

212
00:13:45,603 --> 00:13:47,105
What does that make me, you jerk?

213
00:13:47,188 --> 00:13:48,523
Hey, come on.

214
00:13:48,815 --> 00:13:50,734
Calm down.

215
00:13:50,817 --> 00:13:52,068
How long did you see her for?

216
00:13:52,319 --> 00:13:53,611
Hey!

217
00:13:53,695 --> 00:13:56,990
- You can kill someone with that.
- How many times did you screw her?

218
00:14:38,782 --> 00:14:39,991
911

219
00:14:47,290 --> 00:14:48,291
Is he dead?

220
00:14:53,338 --> 00:14:54,881
Poor guy.

221
00:14:55,965 --> 00:14:56,966
Move him fast.

222
00:15:24,744 --> 00:15:29,457
SEJEONG-RO TRAFFIC ACCIDENT

223
00:15:32,210 --> 00:15:33,878
TRUCK OVERTURNS ON UNDERPASS

224
00:15:33,962 --> 00:15:35,588
TAXI-AMBULANCE COLLISION IN FIRE LANE

225
00:16:32,937 --> 00:16:35,023
Su-jong, how did you find out?

226
00:16:35,273 --> 00:16:37,817
I had such a weird dream last night.

227
00:16:38,610 --> 00:16:39,736
Is he okay?

228
00:16:48,870 --> 00:16:51,414
The MRI results show he's fine.

229
00:16:51,498 --> 00:16:53,541
His blood panel
came back normal, too.

230
00:16:53,958 --> 00:16:55,960
You could call it a miracle.

231
00:16:56,753 --> 00:16:58,880
I've never seen anything like this.

232
00:17:00,340 --> 00:17:01,549
Your husband

233
00:17:02,091 --> 00:17:03,676
left the ward in secret last night

234
00:17:04,427 --> 00:17:06,930
and got into a traffic accident.

235
00:17:07,555 --> 00:17:08,932
He snuck out?

236
00:17:09,015 --> 00:17:10,975
I ran a few tests.

237
00:17:11,059 --> 00:17:12,894
He shows signs of amnesia.

238
00:17:13,228 --> 00:17:16,564
I guess that's why he snuck out.

239
00:17:16,648 --> 00:17:18,066
Memory loss?

240
00:17:18,525 --> 00:17:21,611
The official term is TGA
or transient global amnesia.

241
00:17:22,153 --> 00:17:25,406
Most patients recover in time.

242
00:17:25,490 --> 00:17:27,033
By "most," you mean...

243
00:17:27,325 --> 00:17:31,246
In some instances,
their memory doesn't return.

244
00:17:31,996 --> 00:17:35,083
Fortunately, the collision itself
didn't cause much harm.

245
00:17:36,626 --> 00:17:37,835
Come in.

246
00:17:41,923 --> 00:17:43,049
Yi-gyeong.

247
00:17:43,132 --> 00:17:44,175
No, sit back down.

248
00:17:44,259 --> 00:17:45,468
Sit down.

249
00:17:46,886 --> 00:17:47,971
Goodness.

250
00:17:50,390 --> 00:17:51,516
- Wait.
- What?

251
00:17:52,058 --> 00:17:53,059
Why?

252
00:17:54,185 --> 00:17:55,853
You don't remember?

253
00:17:58,356 --> 00:17:59,774
I really have no idea.

254
00:18:00,567 --> 00:18:01,568
What's the date?

255
00:18:02,235 --> 00:18:05,989
I know that we celebrated
your mother's 70th birthday.

256
00:18:08,741 --> 00:18:11,494
You don't remember I was kidnapped?

257
00:18:13,788 --> 00:18:14,789
Kidnapped?

258
00:18:15,123 --> 00:18:16,666
What the heck has happened?

259
00:18:17,792 --> 00:18:19,043
Are you all right?

260
00:18:19,127 --> 00:18:20,628
Did they catch the culprit?

261
00:18:22,964 --> 00:18:23,965
Hwal-sung.

262
00:18:25,508 --> 00:18:26,509
It's me.

263
00:18:27,510 --> 00:18:28,511
Do you remember me?

264
00:18:30,138 --> 00:18:31,556
Aren't you Mr. Gi Su-jong?

265
00:18:33,891 --> 00:18:35,018
Come on.

266
00:18:35,810 --> 00:18:36,811
Darn you.

267
00:18:36,894 --> 00:18:38,313
How could I not know you?

268
00:18:38,688 --> 00:18:40,189
It's great to see you.

269
00:18:41,649 --> 00:18:42,859
Your mother.

270
00:18:42,942 --> 00:18:45,320
Give her a call.
I should talk to her.

271
00:18:46,404 --> 00:18:47,405
Right?

272
00:18:49,699 --> 00:18:50,700
What?

273
00:18:51,826 --> 00:18:52,952
Is something wrong?

274
00:18:54,370 --> 00:18:55,413
She passed away.

275
00:18:58,666 --> 00:18:59,667
What?

276
00:19:00,168 --> 00:19:01,169
What do you mean?

277
00:19:02,295 --> 00:19:03,921
I'll explain later.

278
00:19:04,714 --> 00:19:06,090
Explain what later?

279
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:11,179
Why would she pass away?

280
00:19:11,971 --> 00:19:14,557
That doesn't make any sense.

281
00:19:22,690 --> 00:19:23,691
What the...

282
00:19:24,359 --> 00:19:25,485
Yi-gyeong.

283
00:19:28,196 --> 00:19:29,322
Mrs. Jeon...

284
00:19:33,534 --> 00:19:34,786
Mrs. Jeon...

285
00:19:38,039 --> 00:19:39,499
Mrs. Jeon...

286
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:45,588
Mrs. Jeon...

287
00:19:48,841 --> 00:19:49,842
Doctor.

288
00:19:51,177 --> 00:19:52,804
When can I go home?

289
00:19:53,304 --> 00:19:54,430
My wife.

290
00:19:55,056 --> 00:19:58,184
I can't let her be home alone.

291
00:19:58,643 --> 00:19:59,769
I need to get out of here.

292
00:20:00,687 --> 00:20:01,688
Please?

293
00:20:04,232 --> 00:20:05,650
I'm sorry.

294
00:20:07,610 --> 00:20:09,237
Hwal-sung woke up?

295
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:10,822
Yes, they say it's a miracle.

296
00:20:12,532 --> 00:20:14,492
Didn't you say he was in a coma?

297
00:20:14,575 --> 00:20:15,993
He suddenly just woke up?

298
00:20:16,244 --> 00:20:18,246
That's why they call it a miracle.

299
00:20:18,329 --> 00:20:19,747
But he lost his memory.

300
00:20:20,373 --> 00:20:21,791
He lost his memory?

301
00:20:22,625 --> 00:20:25,503
It's called transcending
global something.

302
00:20:25,586 --> 00:20:27,130
Transient global amnesia.

303
00:20:27,380 --> 00:20:28,923
Yes, that's it.

304
00:20:29,006 --> 00:20:30,258
Does that actually exist?

305
00:20:30,341 --> 00:20:31,426
Yes.

306
00:20:34,554 --> 00:20:35,555
Hi, Da-rae.

307
00:20:44,147 --> 00:20:46,107
Uncle Hwal-sung's awake.

308
00:20:46,607 --> 00:20:47,942
He's doing okay.

309
00:20:48,484 --> 00:20:51,028
(Really? That's great.)

310
00:20:51,738 --> 00:20:52,822
Yes.

311
00:20:58,536 --> 00:21:03,958
(Why are you two making weird faces?)

312
00:21:06,252 --> 00:21:08,296
She's asking why we look off.

313
00:21:09,213 --> 00:21:10,214
What?

314
00:21:10,715 --> 00:21:12,300
What about us two?

315
00:21:12,383 --> 00:21:15,803
(You look like
you saw something horrible.)

316
00:21:17,305 --> 00:21:19,432
- No, it's fine.
- It's nothing.

317
00:21:19,766 --> 00:21:20,767
Let's eat.

318
00:21:23,644 --> 00:21:25,146
<i>I have something to say.</i>

319
00:21:25,229 --> 00:21:26,272
<i>Are you free?</i>

320
00:21:28,816 --> 00:21:30,026
- Let's eat.
- Okay.

321
00:21:32,945 --> 00:21:33,946
Mrs. Jeon.

322
00:21:40,077 --> 00:21:41,662
Hwal-sung's here to see you.

323
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:46,042
Your idiot son-in-law
took his time...

324
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:50,421
I took my time to visit.

325
00:21:52,965 --> 00:21:54,383
The dream you failed to fulfill.

326
00:21:56,677 --> 00:21:58,346
I'll make it come true for you.

327
00:22:11,692 --> 00:22:14,904
So, what happened to Pyeongbukgwan?

328
00:22:15,696 --> 00:22:17,198
Did you sell it
while I was unconscious?

329
00:22:17,281 --> 00:22:18,699
Why do you care about that?

330
00:22:19,408 --> 00:22:21,327
Your mother passed.

331
00:22:22,620 --> 00:22:24,372
We should manage the assets...

332
00:22:24,455 --> 00:22:25,456
Hwal-sung.

333
00:22:25,915 --> 00:22:26,999
Stay in your place.

334
00:22:30,294 --> 00:22:31,420
What's up with you?

335
00:22:33,422 --> 00:22:35,758
We're married.
We should work together.

336
00:22:39,595 --> 00:22:41,013
I get that you're distraught

337
00:22:41,889 --> 00:22:43,099
because your mother's gone.

338
00:22:44,559 --> 00:22:45,560
But then

339
00:22:46,143 --> 00:22:47,937
if a couple were
to put their heads together

340
00:22:48,020 --> 00:22:49,397
there's nothing
they can't get through.

341
00:22:50,648 --> 00:22:52,775
How could I discuss with a vegetable?

342
00:22:56,112 --> 00:22:57,113
You're right.

343
00:23:00,950 --> 00:23:03,160
But I'm back by your side now.

344
00:23:06,831 --> 00:23:08,291
Aren't you glad I'm awake?

345
00:23:15,339 --> 00:23:16,716
Have some fruit.

346
00:23:22,847 --> 00:23:24,265
You saw her will, didn't you?

347
00:23:24,348 --> 00:23:27,310
I need your signature
regarding the inheritance.

348
00:23:27,810 --> 00:23:29,729
Do I have to read every word?

349
00:23:30,104 --> 00:23:32,106
No, you don't have to.

350
00:23:32,857 --> 00:23:34,525
Your mother had
many different investments.

351
00:23:34,942 --> 00:23:37,737
We have a few issues to handle,
such as taxes.

352
00:23:38,362 --> 00:23:40,031
There are also properties

353
00:23:40,364 --> 00:23:41,574
in the redevelopment area.

354
00:23:42,283 --> 00:23:43,409
Yes.

355
00:23:43,743 --> 00:23:45,578
INHERITOR: JEON YI-GYEONG

356
00:23:46,579 --> 00:23:47,872
PROVISIONAL OWNERS:
JEON YI-GYEONG, MIN HWAL-SUNG

357
00:23:51,542 --> 00:23:53,878
You take care of everything for me.

358
00:23:56,047 --> 00:23:57,048
Okay.

359
00:23:58,674 --> 00:24:00,885
Take care of it for us.

360
00:24:01,802 --> 00:24:03,679
I'll call when it's taken care of.

361
00:24:12,772 --> 00:24:16,609
You should carefully read
papers like that before signing.

362
00:24:16,859 --> 00:24:17,860
You never know.

363
00:24:17,944 --> 00:24:19,362
You never know what?

364
00:24:19,695 --> 00:24:22,198
He worked with Mom for a long time.

365
00:24:22,823 --> 00:24:24,742
I'll take care of it. Don't mind it.

366
00:24:26,953 --> 00:24:30,623
I'm sure you'll take care of it.

367
00:24:37,505 --> 00:24:38,506
Have some fruit.

368
00:24:42,843 --> 00:24:44,178
I'll go wash my hands.

369
00:24:55,731 --> 00:24:57,566
<i>Good job, Lawyer Yang.</i>

370
00:24:58,025 --> 00:24:59,026
<i>See you soon.</i>

371
00:25:06,534 --> 00:25:07,743
<i>Did you read my DM?</i>

372
00:25:09,161 --> 00:25:10,287
<i>Let's meet.</i>

373
00:25:22,466 --> 00:25:24,552
<i>Can you keep tabs on someone for me?</i>

374
00:25:25,761 --> 00:25:26,762
Who?

375
00:25:27,013 --> 00:25:28,014
My husband.

376
00:25:30,599 --> 00:25:32,435
Yes, I think I'm at the right place.

377
00:25:33,686 --> 00:25:34,687
Where are you?

378
00:25:35,354 --> 00:25:36,480
<i>In the third booth.</i>

379
00:25:36,814 --> 00:25:37,857
The third booth.

380
00:25:44,905 --> 00:25:46,323
What's that reaction for?

381
00:25:46,907 --> 00:25:47,908
Take a seat.

382
00:25:48,951 --> 00:25:49,952
This is for you.

383
00:25:50,036 --> 00:25:51,746
- It's fine.
- It's not fine.

384
00:25:52,371 --> 00:25:53,622
Look at what I'm wearing.

385
00:25:57,209 --> 00:25:58,210
So.

386
00:25:59,253 --> 00:26:01,464
You look much better
now that my mother-in-law's dead.

387
00:26:02,089 --> 00:26:03,299
Thank you.

388
00:26:03,841 --> 00:26:05,509
No one knows you embezzled yet?

389
00:26:06,177 --> 00:26:08,929
Why would you bring that up
all of a sudden?

390
00:26:09,722 --> 00:26:11,015
Did you update

391
00:26:11,098 --> 00:26:12,725
the inheritance documents as I said?

392
00:26:13,851 --> 00:26:14,852
Yes.

393
00:26:15,186 --> 00:26:17,605
Soon, they'll be put in your name.

394
00:26:18,272 --> 00:26:19,273
Good.

395
00:26:20,483 --> 00:26:23,110
Will this really be okay?

396
00:26:24,445 --> 00:26:25,654
Of course.

397
00:26:27,239 --> 00:26:29,575
Trust me. I have a plan.

398
00:26:30,618 --> 00:26:31,619
Get up.

399
00:26:31,702 --> 00:26:33,037
Let's take a photo as a souvenir.

400
00:26:33,120 --> 00:26:34,205
Try it on.

401
00:26:35,206 --> 00:26:36,290
- It suits you.
- Are you kidding me?

402
00:27:00,314 --> 00:27:01,941
It's a mess.

403
00:27:02,399 --> 00:27:04,068
The circuit breaker keeps tripping,
doesn't it?

404
00:27:05,861 --> 00:27:07,988
It's because of the leak.

405
00:27:09,198 --> 00:27:12,034
How much will the repair cost?

406
00:27:12,576 --> 00:27:14,453
This is a bad case.

407
00:27:14,537 --> 00:27:18,082
The water tank and breaker box
both need to be fixed.

408
00:27:18,666 --> 00:27:20,584
So how much?

409
00:27:21,085 --> 00:27:23,003
They're all so old.

410
00:27:23,087 --> 00:27:25,089
Why are you so hesitant to answer?

411
00:27:26,590 --> 00:27:28,217
It'll cost about ten.

412
00:27:28,634 --> 00:27:30,302
- Ten million?
- Yes.

413
00:27:30,386 --> 00:27:32,680
That's on the cheaper side.

414
00:27:33,222 --> 00:27:34,557
For now

415
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:36,559
do what you can to get the lights on.

416
00:27:37,309 --> 00:27:40,229
I can do the bare minimum
to solve that issue

417
00:27:40,312 --> 00:27:42,273
but it can be
really dangerous later on.

418
00:27:42,356 --> 00:27:44,275
Everything needs replacing.

419
00:27:44,358 --> 00:27:46,318
Okay, I'll take care of that later.

420
00:27:46,402 --> 00:27:49,238
Take some emergency measures for now.

421
00:27:49,989 --> 00:27:51,615
It's so darn old.

422
00:27:54,034 --> 00:27:55,828
Replace the whole system later, okay?

423
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:57,538
- Okay.
- Bye.

424
00:27:57,621 --> 00:27:59,373
Thank you. Bye.

425
00:28:02,251 --> 00:28:04,461
I don't have ten million won.

426
00:28:20,728 --> 00:28:21,812
What the heck?

427
00:28:21,896 --> 00:28:24,315
Gosh, you're so very busy.

428
00:28:24,940 --> 00:28:25,941
What are you doing here?

429
00:28:27,318 --> 00:28:29,361
- The place smells.
- What?

430
00:28:30,571 --> 00:28:31,947
Is it because it's the basement?

431
00:28:51,550 --> 00:28:52,885
Where are we going?

432
00:28:53,510 --> 00:28:54,720
Do you have any last words?

433
00:28:55,512 --> 00:28:56,513
What?

434
00:28:56,847 --> 00:29:00,267
The final words you wish
to leave to your family.

435
00:29:07,107 --> 00:29:08,400
I'm kidding.

436
00:29:13,113 --> 00:29:15,532
Deputy Nam wants to see us.

437
00:29:17,034 --> 00:29:18,661
You work with Deputy Nam?

438
00:29:18,953 --> 00:29:19,954
Since when?

439
00:29:20,871 --> 00:29:21,872
Jonah.

440
00:29:23,666 --> 00:29:25,834
That's my name.
Do you know what it means?

441
00:29:26,794 --> 00:29:27,795
Jonah.

442
00:29:29,797 --> 00:29:31,548
"The bringer of misfortune."

443
00:29:33,968 --> 00:29:34,969
So what?

444
00:29:35,302 --> 00:29:36,387
Do you remember?

445
00:29:37,221 --> 00:29:41,308
"The pain that doesn't kill you
only makes you stronger."

446
00:29:42,977 --> 00:29:44,186
What does that mean?

447
00:29:45,771 --> 00:29:48,399
Call me whenever you need help.

448
00:29:55,281 --> 00:29:57,533
PYEONGBUKGWAN HAS
A LONG TRADITION IN SEJEONG-RO...

449
00:30:00,494 --> 00:30:01,745
You're friends with him, right?

450
00:30:02,162 --> 00:30:04,498
Yes, we're best friends.
We go way back.

451
00:30:05,082 --> 00:30:06,292
What now?

452
00:30:07,418 --> 00:30:09,211
What if he refuses to sell?

453
00:30:09,295 --> 00:30:10,963
He's all talk and no action.

454
00:30:11,046 --> 00:30:12,256
You don't have to worry.

455
00:30:13,507 --> 00:30:16,719
Why can't I reach the daughter?

456
00:30:16,802 --> 00:30:18,554
I offered extra money,
yet she still wouldn't answer.

457
00:30:19,221 --> 00:30:20,472
Is this a Gen Z thing?

458
00:30:20,806 --> 00:30:23,183
You must handle Pyeongbukgwan wisely.

459
00:30:23,559 --> 00:30:25,227
You should let her keep her pride.

460
00:30:26,645 --> 00:30:29,064
Take over Pyeongbukgwan.

461
00:30:30,399 --> 00:30:31,525
Goodness.

462
00:30:31,608 --> 00:30:33,944
I have the money, so persuade her.

463
00:30:34,486 --> 00:30:37,406
Do your best
to let her pride stand tall.

464
00:30:41,952 --> 00:30:43,370
Well, I'll require some shares.

465
00:30:44,288 --> 00:30:45,789
- Shares?
- Yes.

466
00:30:46,623 --> 00:30:48,250
If I convince Pyeongbukgwan

467
00:30:49,293 --> 00:30:50,753
I'm taking half the shares.

468
00:30:51,587 --> 00:30:54,506
I've already convinced Hanmaeum,
so if I also took Pyeongbukgwan over

469
00:30:55,049 --> 00:30:57,718
it would mean I got my hands
on most of the altered zone.

470
00:30:57,968 --> 00:30:59,928
So of course, I'll need more shares.

471
00:31:02,556 --> 00:31:04,975
Mr. Gi, I didn't know you liked
to live life in the fast lane.

472
00:31:05,059 --> 00:31:06,435
I wouldn't say that.

473
00:31:10,230 --> 00:31:11,231
Sure.

474
00:31:12,441 --> 00:31:13,484
I'll consider it.

475
00:31:13,567 --> 00:31:15,069
Yes, do consider it.

476
00:31:15,152 --> 00:31:16,695
Please excuse me.

477
00:31:16,779 --> 00:31:18,197
By the way.

478
00:31:18,655 --> 00:31:19,656
Are you free tomorrow?

479
00:31:21,408 --> 00:31:22,951
Tomorrow? What is it?

480
00:31:35,506 --> 00:31:37,049
What is this?
Are you getting married?

481
00:31:39,968 --> 00:31:42,971
It's a couple's night,
so make sure you dress up.

482
00:31:43,764 --> 00:31:44,765
You may go now.

483
00:31:45,099 --> 00:31:46,100
Yes, okay.

484
00:31:58,487 --> 00:31:59,905
You heard that punk talk, right?

485
00:32:00,489 --> 00:32:01,490
This is why

486
00:32:01,573 --> 00:32:03,784
you never take someone in
and show them a favor.

487
00:32:04,284 --> 00:32:06,829
Get rid of him once the job is done.

488
00:32:13,877 --> 00:32:14,878
Did you hear me?

489
00:32:17,840 --> 00:32:18,841
I did.

490
00:32:18,924 --> 00:32:20,134
I'll handle him.

491
00:32:24,346 --> 00:32:25,347
Su-jong.

492
00:32:25,431 --> 00:32:26,849
Do I have to go?

493
00:32:27,307 --> 00:32:28,642
Yes, of course.

494
00:32:31,645 --> 00:32:33,730
Why do I only have sweatsuits?

495
00:32:34,982 --> 00:32:37,192
Seon, where's my suit jacket?

496
00:32:37,901 --> 00:32:40,529
It's all the way in the box
under the blanket.

497
00:32:49,580 --> 00:32:51,498
Is this too much? What do you think?

498
00:32:54,877 --> 00:32:56,587
Hey, Seon. You look gorgeous.

499
00:32:57,713 --> 00:32:59,882
Cut it out. Do I really look okay?

500
00:33:02,426 --> 00:33:03,635
Darn it.

501
00:33:04,136 --> 00:33:06,054
Since you're pretty,
you and Hwal-sung... Darn it.

502
00:33:08,056 --> 00:33:09,892
Why are you suddenly going there?

503
00:33:11,435 --> 00:33:12,853
I was randomly reminded of it.

504
00:33:14,188 --> 00:33:16,106
You and Hwal-sung would...

505
00:33:17,941 --> 00:33:19,026
Darn it.

506
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:21,361
Su-jong.

507
00:33:22,571 --> 00:33:24,323
It's time to put it out of your mind.

508
00:33:24,406 --> 00:33:25,532
Get rid of it.

509
00:33:26,325 --> 00:33:27,326
Okay?

510
00:33:29,578 --> 00:33:31,246
- Okay?
- Yes, fine.

511
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:38,837
Okay, let's get ready and leave.

512
00:33:39,129 --> 00:33:40,255
- Okay?
- Okay.

513
00:33:40,339 --> 00:33:41,340
- Put it on.
- Okay.

514
00:33:55,145 --> 00:33:56,146
LOAN HEAVEN

515
00:34:05,531 --> 00:34:06,615
You're almost done.

516
00:34:08,200 --> 00:34:09,201
Hey.

517
00:34:10,118 --> 00:34:12,037
Seon told me about you.

518
00:34:12,371 --> 00:34:13,622
How many weeks are you in?

519
00:34:13,705 --> 00:34:15,249
It's a little over two months.

520
00:34:16,124 --> 00:34:18,877
Take good care of yourself early on
to have a safe delivery later.

521
00:34:19,461 --> 00:34:20,921
Stop by occasionally for the shots.

522
00:34:21,004 --> 00:34:22,422
I'll give it to you at cost.

523
00:34:23,173 --> 00:34:24,675
Hold this.

524
00:34:27,135 --> 00:34:28,762
That's a vitamin.

525
00:34:28,845 --> 00:34:29,846
It's on the house.

526
00:34:30,764 --> 00:34:31,765
Thank you.

527
00:34:31,848 --> 00:34:33,183
You can thank Seon.

528
00:34:33,267 --> 00:34:34,268
Excuse me.

529
00:34:34,851 --> 00:34:36,812
I have a favor to ask you.

530
00:34:39,106 --> 00:34:41,567
Can I find some anesthesia?

531
00:34:42,234 --> 00:34:43,235
Anesthesia?

532
00:34:44,236 --> 00:34:45,862
I know you've made
a similar deal before

533
00:34:46,738 --> 00:34:48,156
with someone named Min Hwal-sung.

534
00:34:49,700 --> 00:34:50,951
He's my husband.

535
00:34:52,244 --> 00:34:53,245
Can you do that?

536
00:34:56,290 --> 00:34:57,708
OH DONG-KI

537
00:34:59,084 --> 00:35:00,877
PREVIOUS CHARGES: NONE

538
00:35:00,961 --> 00:35:02,963
No criminal records.

539
00:35:04,756 --> 00:35:06,300
POSTMORTEM REPORT

540
00:35:06,383 --> 00:35:07,551
COMMENT FROM THE EXAMINER

541
00:35:07,634 --> 00:35:09,845
A FATAL GUNSHOT IN THE HEART...
BRUISES AND SIGNS OF BEATING...

542
00:35:09,928 --> 00:35:12,014
THERE ARE SIGNS OF TETANUS
CAUSING NECROSIS IN THE TISSUE...

543
00:35:27,487 --> 00:35:29,531
I know something is up
with Gi Su-jong.

544
00:35:30,991 --> 00:35:31,992
Ju-ran.

545
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:37,456
We're done with that case.
Why are you stressing out?

546
00:35:37,539 --> 00:35:41,043
You also said
Mr. Gi seemed suspicious.

547
00:35:41,293 --> 00:35:42,794
But we found all the evidence.

548
00:35:44,421 --> 00:35:45,589
Right?

549
00:35:46,715 --> 00:35:49,134
We did find all the evidence.

550
00:35:50,552 --> 00:35:52,387
You should take a few days off
and get a good rest.

551
00:35:52,888 --> 00:35:53,889
Right.

552
00:35:53,972 --> 00:35:55,390
Someone is out there,
looking for you.

553
00:35:57,225 --> 00:35:58,226
Who?

554
00:35:58,644 --> 00:36:01,605
SEOUL YONGDAEMUN POLICE STATION

555
00:36:14,660 --> 00:36:16,286
I heard Mr. Min woke up.

556
00:36:22,918 --> 00:36:24,836
I want to check
if this is the same drug

557
00:36:24,920 --> 00:36:26,922
they used when I was kidnapped.

558
00:36:27,297 --> 00:36:28,507
Is that possible?

559
00:36:41,770 --> 00:36:42,771
Go ahead.

560
00:36:44,898 --> 00:36:46,525
The current shares...

561
00:36:48,235 --> 00:36:49,236
You're here.

562
00:36:49,319 --> 00:36:50,362
You can sit over there.

563
00:36:50,612 --> 00:36:51,613
Yes, okay.

564
00:36:52,823 --> 00:36:54,157
Please help yourself.

565
00:37:03,291 --> 00:37:04,376
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

566
00:37:04,835 --> 00:37:06,670
ASSETS PORTFOLIO

567
00:37:09,089 --> 00:37:10,590
Please meet Mr. Gi Su-jong.

568
00:37:10,674 --> 00:37:12,092
- Hello.
- Of Se-yoon Building.

569
00:37:12,843 --> 00:37:14,845
He's a building owner

570
00:37:15,429 --> 00:37:18,432
who has been playing a big part
in the Sejeong-ro Project.

571
00:37:18,515 --> 00:37:19,808
- A great young man.
- He got Hanmaeum as well.

572
00:37:20,267 --> 00:37:21,268
Please meet her.

573
00:37:21,643 --> 00:37:22,644
Hello.

574
00:37:22,978 --> 00:37:25,522
I'm so sorry that I couldn't make it
to your son's wedding.

575
00:37:26,481 --> 00:37:27,482
Meet her. So, your son...

576
00:37:30,402 --> 00:37:31,653
Why are you ignoring me?

577
00:37:32,904 --> 00:37:33,905
Why?

578
00:37:34,448 --> 00:37:36,366
You should be glad I ignored you.

579
00:37:38,034 --> 00:37:39,161
Don't be so hard on me.

580
00:37:40,579 --> 00:37:42,330
Hey, I came back from the dead.

581
00:37:42,789 --> 00:37:45,083
Shouldn't you be
a little worried about me?

582
00:37:47,586 --> 00:37:49,880
Sure, I'm glad you woke up.

583
00:37:51,715 --> 00:37:54,134
- Were you there, Hee-ju?
- I went.

584
00:37:54,217 --> 00:37:55,761
Su-jong knows about us.

585
00:37:56,928 --> 00:37:57,929
Are you going to divorce him?

586
00:38:00,015 --> 00:38:01,099
What's wrong with you?

587
00:38:01,433 --> 00:38:02,934
If you do, let's start over together.

588
00:38:04,019 --> 00:38:05,020
I mean it.

589
00:38:07,022 --> 00:38:08,023
Have you lost your mind?

590
00:38:09,399 --> 00:38:10,901
I heard you had amnesia.

591
00:38:12,527 --> 00:38:16,156
Do you really not remember anything?

592
00:38:17,866 --> 00:38:18,867
Is it that obvious?

593
00:38:20,577 --> 00:38:22,704
I thought I had put on a good act.

594
00:38:24,414 --> 00:38:26,333
I did it because of Su-jong.

595
00:38:27,250 --> 00:38:28,919
That punk tried to kill me.

596
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:32,380
Mr. Gi is great at doing business.

597
00:38:40,222 --> 00:38:41,473
Let me tell you a secret.

598
00:38:42,265 --> 00:38:45,227
Su-jong was the one
who kidnapped Yi-gyeong.

599
00:38:47,395 --> 00:38:49,397
He's also the one
who killed my mother-in-law.

600
00:38:50,148 --> 00:38:52,776
He tried to kill me
because I caught onto everything.

601
00:38:54,611 --> 00:38:55,737
So today...

602
00:38:58,990 --> 00:39:00,534
We need to work together.

603
00:39:01,535 --> 00:39:02,619
Why should we?

604
00:39:06,456 --> 00:39:08,291
I'm going to divorce Yi-gyeong.

605
00:39:09,543 --> 00:39:10,961
We'll both get divorced

606
00:39:12,712 --> 00:39:14,005
and take over

607
00:39:14,881 --> 00:39:16,091
the redevelopment project.

608
00:39:17,717 --> 00:39:19,261
With the right plan

609
00:39:19,845 --> 00:39:21,054
we can pull it off.

610
00:39:21,721 --> 00:39:22,889
Hwal-sung.

611
00:39:23,557 --> 00:39:24,558
Yes?

612
00:39:28,228 --> 00:39:30,105
You were the kidnapper.

613
00:39:32,232 --> 00:39:33,775
I already know what's going on.

614
00:39:33,859 --> 00:39:36,361
I know what you
and Su-jong have done.

615
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:41,283
Okay.

616
00:39:42,367 --> 00:39:44,202
There seems to be a misunderstanding.

617
00:39:45,871 --> 00:39:47,289
We can discuss this later.

618
00:39:51,376 --> 00:39:52,794
I bet you didn't know this.

619
00:39:54,462 --> 00:39:56,882
Su-jong has something to do
with Gyun's death.

620
00:40:00,677 --> 00:40:01,761
What are you talking about?

621
00:40:03,847 --> 00:40:05,557
Do you remember that time

622
00:40:05,807 --> 00:40:08,184
when he almost lost Se-yoon Building
in an auction?

623
00:40:08,768 --> 00:40:10,312
He went around
trying to borrow money.

624
00:40:10,395 --> 00:40:11,605
<i>Do you think we can take out</i>

625
00:40:11,688 --> 00:40:13,607
another loan
against Se-yoon Building?

626
00:40:13,690 --> 00:40:14,816
I've pulled all the loans I could

627
00:40:14,900 --> 00:40:16,985
but you can get some more, right?

628
00:40:17,444 --> 00:40:19,946
Gyun tried to help Su-jong out

629
00:40:20,614 --> 00:40:22,240
and ended up like that.

630
00:40:24,284 --> 00:40:26,620
Everyone in Sejeong-ro
has heard about it.

631
00:40:26,912 --> 00:40:30,332
Gyun died because of Su-jong?

632
00:40:31,625 --> 00:40:32,751
How can I...

633
00:40:33,251 --> 00:40:35,086
I can't bring myself to say that.

634
00:40:35,795 --> 00:40:37,005
Ask him yourself.

635
00:40:40,175 --> 00:40:41,259
Kim Gyun?

636
00:40:42,052 --> 00:40:43,470
You were at the scene
of Gyun's accident

637
00:40:43,762 --> 00:40:44,763
weren't you?

638
00:40:45,513 --> 00:40:46,640
Let's go, Su-jong.

639
00:40:49,351 --> 00:40:50,352
Hello, friend.

640
00:40:52,729 --> 00:40:53,813
- What brings you here?
- What?

641
00:40:55,065 --> 00:40:56,274
I just stopped by.

642
00:40:58,693 --> 00:40:59,778
What did you two talk about?

643
00:41:00,904 --> 00:41:02,030
You, obviously.

644
00:41:03,031 --> 00:41:04,658
It's the most fun
to talk behind someone's back

645
00:41:04,741 --> 00:41:07,035
when they have stepped away
for a brief moment.

646
00:41:09,579 --> 00:41:11,581
You punk. That's not even funny.

647
00:41:12,040 --> 00:41:14,459
Don't call your friend a punk,
you punk.

648
00:41:15,377 --> 00:41:16,878
Are you trying to hit me again?

649
00:41:17,128 --> 00:41:18,213
Or trying to kill me again?

650
00:41:19,839 --> 00:41:20,840
Hwal-sung.

651
00:41:22,050 --> 00:41:23,093
You...

652
00:41:24,511 --> 00:41:25,595
remember, right?

653
00:41:27,597 --> 00:41:28,598
What?

654
00:41:29,182 --> 00:41:31,267
Was there something
that I should have remembered?

655
00:41:32,769 --> 00:41:34,145
Goodness, Mr. Min.

656
00:41:34,437 --> 00:41:35,689
Oh, my.

657
00:41:35,772 --> 00:41:36,982
Hello, Mr. Nam.

658
00:41:37,983 --> 00:41:40,485
I heard you had been fatally wounded.

659
00:41:41,152 --> 00:41:42,362
I've resurrected.

660
00:41:44,948 --> 00:41:45,949
Mr. Min!

661
00:41:46,032 --> 00:41:47,659
Goodness, Hee-ju.

662
00:41:47,742 --> 00:41:48,994
It's been a while.

663
00:41:50,078 --> 00:41:52,914
Did you know that Hwal-sung lied
about losing his memories?

664
00:41:53,957 --> 00:41:55,291
I found out just now.

665
00:41:55,959 --> 00:41:57,585
Did you really find out just now?

666
00:41:58,795 --> 00:42:00,171
Are you suspicious of me?

667
00:42:00,880 --> 00:42:01,881
No.

668
00:42:03,717 --> 00:42:05,552
Anyway, did you call him here today?

669
00:42:05,635 --> 00:42:07,178
Why would I do that?

670
00:42:07,512 --> 00:42:08,930
What were you two whispering about?

671
00:42:10,765 --> 00:42:12,100
Enough is enough.

672
00:42:12,392 --> 00:42:13,393
Stop acting like you have

673
00:42:13,476 --> 00:42:14,894
- something on me.
- What do you mean?

674
00:42:14,978 --> 00:42:17,188
Look at the way you're acting.

675
00:42:17,272 --> 00:42:20,025
You pry, ask, and nitpick over things
to make me feel guilty.

676
00:42:20,984 --> 00:42:21,985
What do you want?

677
00:42:22,444 --> 00:42:23,987
Do you want me to feel helpless?

678
00:42:24,320 --> 00:42:26,406
I'm tormented too, but what can I do?

679
00:42:26,489 --> 00:42:27,907
It's all in the past.

680
00:42:29,409 --> 00:42:31,411
How can you be so cold?

681
00:42:31,995 --> 00:42:33,705
How can you talk like that?

682
00:42:33,788 --> 00:42:35,415
You just hurt me greatly.

683
00:42:37,333 --> 00:42:38,752
Let's set the record straight.

684
00:42:38,835 --> 00:42:40,920
I had an affair and hurt you?

685
00:42:41,004 --> 00:42:42,338
What about you?

686
00:42:42,756 --> 00:42:44,716
- You kidnapped your friend's wife.
- Hey!

687
00:42:49,220 --> 00:42:50,430
And you...

688
00:42:50,513 --> 00:42:51,514
What?

689
00:42:52,265 --> 00:42:53,266
Never mind.

690
00:42:54,934 --> 00:42:57,270
My life is miserable enough as it is.

691
00:42:57,353 --> 00:43:00,106
So, stop messing with me.

692
00:43:04,152 --> 00:43:05,987
Sir, will you let me off here
for a moment?

693
00:43:17,457 --> 00:43:18,750
Darn it.

694
00:43:24,380 --> 00:43:27,801
YI-GYEONG

695
00:43:36,059 --> 00:43:38,311
Hello, Yi-gyeong. It's me.

696
00:43:40,063 --> 00:43:42,482
I have something to say to you.

697
00:43:42,941 --> 00:43:45,110
PYEONGBUKGWAN

698
00:43:48,863 --> 00:43:49,864
MY DAUGHTER

699
00:43:49,948 --> 00:43:51,116
WHERE ARE YOU, DAD?
I'M ON MY WAY TO YOUR BUILDING

700
00:43:54,744 --> 00:43:56,496
<i>I came out for a moment.</i>
<i>I'll text you later.</i>

701
00:44:04,754 --> 00:44:05,839
Hello, Yi-gyeong.

702
00:44:06,881 --> 00:44:07,882
Have a seat.

703
00:44:08,133 --> 00:44:09,134
Sure.

704
00:44:17,058 --> 00:44:18,059
Now.

705
00:44:18,518 --> 00:44:19,686
SEJEONG-RO INVESTMENT CORPORATION

706
00:44:19,769 --> 00:44:21,729
So here's the thing.

707
00:44:22,438 --> 00:44:25,567
The biggest office building in Asia
will be erected in this area.

708
00:44:26,526 --> 00:44:27,735
And Pyeongbukgwan will have

709
00:44:27,819 --> 00:44:31,739
its place on the first floor
as a representative Korean brand.

710
00:44:31,823 --> 00:44:34,826
It'll be a great opportunity
to globalize the business.

711
00:44:35,577 --> 00:44:38,246
I'm sure Madam Jeon
would have loved that.

712
00:44:38,663 --> 00:44:40,331
Is this about Nouveau City?

713
00:44:40,748 --> 00:44:42,417
The one Mr. Nam is involved in.

714
00:44:42,876 --> 00:44:44,335
Yes, you've heard about it?

715
00:44:45,003 --> 00:44:47,839
It's funny to hear about
Pyeongbukgwan's renewal from you.

716
00:44:49,674 --> 00:44:51,217
Yi-gyeong, I...

717
00:44:51,301 --> 00:44:53,219
I'll talk to him

718
00:44:53,636 --> 00:44:56,431
and give you a good price
for the building.

719
00:44:57,056 --> 00:44:59,559
So please give me your trust

720
00:44:59,642 --> 00:45:00,768
and join the project.

721
00:45:01,102 --> 00:45:02,854
Why are you trying so hard?

722
00:45:04,731 --> 00:45:05,899
Because of money?

723
00:45:07,775 --> 00:45:08,776
I don't know.

724
00:45:09,736 --> 00:45:12,572
I guess it's because of Da-rae.

725
00:45:12,655 --> 00:45:13,656
Right, Da-rae.

726
00:45:14,616 --> 00:45:16,868
I'm sure she means the most to you.

727
00:45:18,995 --> 00:45:20,914
The contract works for me.

728
00:45:22,040 --> 00:45:24,042
But I have a question
before we proceed.

729
00:45:25,627 --> 00:45:27,921
LOAN HEAVEN

730
00:45:28,213 --> 00:45:30,965
Did you know about them?

731
00:45:36,721 --> 00:45:37,847
DETECTIVE KOH JU-RAN

732
00:45:41,267 --> 00:45:42,268
Hello, Detective.

733
00:45:43,353 --> 00:45:44,771
<i>They're the same anesthetic agent.</i>

734
00:45:45,813 --> 00:45:47,732
<i>I'd like to open</i>
<i>an official investigation.</i>

735
00:45:47,815 --> 00:45:49,901
<i>May I ask how you came to get this?</i>

736
00:45:55,823 --> 00:45:57,033
Something's going on, right?

737
00:45:57,659 --> 00:45:58,660
No.

738
00:45:59,160 --> 00:46:00,578
No, it's nothing like that.

739
00:46:01,496 --> 00:46:02,580
<i>Sorry?</i>

740
00:46:03,414 --> 00:46:05,250
I'll reach out to you later.

741
00:46:09,879 --> 00:46:11,422
BENZODIAZEPINE WAS FOUND IN THE DRUG

742
00:46:11,506 --> 00:46:13,258
Hwal-sung had bought
an anesthetic drug

743
00:46:14,133 --> 00:46:16,135
at the hospital
Seon hooked me up with.

744
00:46:18,638 --> 00:46:20,056
Be honest with me.

745
00:46:20,515 --> 00:46:21,516
Did you two...

746
00:46:30,692 --> 00:46:31,693
Yes.

747
00:46:32,735 --> 00:46:34,070
We kidnapped you.

748
00:46:38,074 --> 00:46:41,911
I should've told you this earlier.

749
00:46:42,829 --> 00:46:43,830
I'm sorry.

750
00:46:45,331 --> 00:46:48,960
Seon was involved in this

751
00:46:49,711 --> 00:46:51,045
so I was quite stumped.

752
00:46:55,341 --> 00:46:57,677
So you knew
they were seeing each other?

753
00:46:59,262 --> 00:47:00,263
Yes.

754
00:47:00,805 --> 00:47:02,015
It must've been hard.

755
00:47:04,142 --> 00:47:05,143
It was.

756
00:47:09,522 --> 00:47:10,523
But still

757
00:47:11,482 --> 00:47:12,900
she's Da-rae's mother.

758
00:47:14,444 --> 00:47:16,070
I know it's brazen of me to ask

759
00:47:17,363 --> 00:47:20,616
but I don't want
Seon to end up in prison.

760
00:47:21,701 --> 00:47:26,539
This was Hwal-sung's plan all along.

761
00:47:33,838 --> 00:47:35,048
How intriguing.

762
00:47:35,423 --> 00:47:36,424
Yi-gyeong.

763
00:47:36,883 --> 00:47:38,384
Please, I'm asking you.

764
00:47:38,885 --> 00:47:40,094
I know it makes no sense.

765
00:47:42,263 --> 00:47:44,349
But can you please forgive her

766
00:47:44,432 --> 00:47:45,641
for Da-rae's sake?

767
00:47:50,897 --> 00:47:52,315
I've recently come to realize

768
00:47:54,025 --> 00:47:55,860
how much Seon truly loves Da-rae.

769
00:47:59,405 --> 00:48:01,741
Your child will also grow up

770
00:48:01,824 --> 00:48:03,284
healthy and beautiful like you.

771
00:48:03,368 --> 00:48:04,410
But the kid won't have a dad.

772
00:48:05,536 --> 00:48:06,537
Just like me.

773
00:48:16,255 --> 00:48:17,757
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

774
00:48:42,573 --> 00:48:43,574
<i>Da-rae.</i>

775
00:48:43,991 --> 00:48:45,910
<i>The acceptance e-mail</i>
<i>just came from Harvard.</i>

776
00:49:04,595 --> 00:49:09,267
MY GOSH... WHAT DO I DO?

777
00:49:15,189 --> 00:49:16,274
<i>Should we click on it together?</i>

778
00:49:16,357 --> 00:49:18,985
YES

779
00:49:40,339 --> 00:49:41,382
<i>Did you get in?</i>

780
00:49:41,466 --> 00:49:47,513
YES! WHAT ABOUT YOU?

781
00:49:56,606 --> 00:49:59,150
<i>I didn't get in.</i>

782
00:50:04,030 --> 00:50:05,031
OH NO

783
00:50:05,114 --> 00:50:06,991
<i>It's okay.</i>
<i>I'll get into another school.</i>

784
00:50:07,074 --> 00:50:09,118
<i>Congratulations, Da-rae!</i>
<i>This is great!</i>

785
00:50:09,202 --> 00:50:10,203
THANK YOU

786
00:50:17,877 --> 00:50:19,378
UNKNOWN ERROR
CLOSE THE PAGE AND RETRY

787
00:50:28,054 --> 00:50:29,305
LOADING
PLEASE WAIT

788
00:52:10,072 --> 00:52:11,157
Mr. Gi?

789
00:52:11,532 --> 00:52:13,534
Hey, what are you doing?

790
00:52:14,076 --> 00:52:16,412
You aren't allowed to drink
at a convenience store these days.

791
00:52:16,495 --> 00:52:17,496
Is that so?

792
00:52:20,082 --> 00:52:21,917
I have something nice at my office.

793
00:52:22,543 --> 00:52:23,544
Come with me.

794
00:52:26,672 --> 00:52:27,673
Okay, sure.

795
00:52:43,689 --> 00:52:45,191
Yi-gyeong, I'm home.

796
00:52:51,197 --> 00:52:52,198
Yi-gyeong.

797
00:52:53,324 --> 00:52:54,659
I need to talk to you.

798
00:52:56,452 --> 00:52:57,453
What?

799
00:52:58,245 --> 00:52:59,789
I'm tired, let me just...

800
00:53:00,122 --> 00:53:01,791
- Can I wash up quickly?
- No.

801
00:53:02,333 --> 00:53:03,334
Right now.

802
00:53:10,216 --> 00:53:11,425
Where have you been?

803
00:53:14,011 --> 00:53:15,221
I had to meet someone.

804
00:53:15,304 --> 00:53:17,056
I asked, where have you been?

805
00:53:20,726 --> 00:53:22,645
There was an event
with the redevelopment project

806
00:53:22,728 --> 00:53:24,355
so I went there.

807
00:53:24,438 --> 00:53:25,439
Why?

808
00:53:26,691 --> 00:53:28,317
To sell Pyeongbukgwan away?

809
00:53:29,652 --> 00:53:31,570
Does anybody there
even listen to you?

810
00:53:35,074 --> 00:53:36,325
Jeez.

811
00:53:37,868 --> 00:53:39,161
Do you really think

812
00:53:39,745 --> 00:53:41,247
I'm that dumb?

813
00:53:42,373 --> 00:53:43,791
I have my own plan.

814
00:53:43,874 --> 00:53:46,210
You'd be helping much more
if you didn't do anything.

815
00:53:46,293 --> 00:53:48,295
Just sit around still like a stone.

816
00:53:51,340 --> 00:53:53,801
I should've stayed in bed
as a vegetable.

817
00:53:54,885 --> 00:53:56,387
Why did I wake up?

818
00:53:57,638 --> 00:53:58,639
Sorry.

819
00:54:01,809 --> 00:54:05,146
But you also are unbelievable.

820
00:54:05,521 --> 00:54:07,273
You always hated your mother.

821
00:54:08,607 --> 00:54:10,818
And you said her <i>naengmyeon</i>
tasted like mop water.

822
00:54:11,318 --> 00:54:12,820
What are you trying to do now?

823
00:54:14,029 --> 00:54:15,030
Be a good daughter?

824
00:54:28,210 --> 00:54:29,587
Have you been cheating with Seon?

825
00:54:31,046 --> 00:54:32,047
Hey.

826
00:54:33,632 --> 00:54:35,718
We just met by chance and had a chat.

827
00:54:35,801 --> 00:54:36,802
What about the kidnapping?

828
00:54:38,888 --> 00:54:39,889
What are you talking about?

829
00:54:41,724 --> 00:54:42,725
Hey.

830
00:54:48,647 --> 00:54:50,983
You were much better
when you were a vegetable.

831
00:54:56,363 --> 00:54:57,698
I can explain.

832
00:55:00,367 --> 00:55:01,786
Get out of my house.

833
00:55:04,246 --> 00:55:05,664
What do you mean, Yi-gyeong?

834
00:55:05,748 --> 00:55:07,249
Get out of here!

835
00:55:26,560 --> 00:55:27,978
KIM GYUN

836
00:55:28,896 --> 00:55:30,147
<i>I bet you didn't know this.</i>

837
00:55:30,397 --> 00:55:32,399
Su-jong has something to do
with Gyun's death.

838
00:55:38,322 --> 00:55:39,448
Hey, Da-rae.

839
00:55:52,044 --> 00:55:53,838
I WANT TO BE ALONE

840
00:55:53,921 --> 00:55:57,925
IS SOMETHING GOING ON?

841
00:56:03,848 --> 00:56:05,266
What's with her?

842
00:56:05,349 --> 00:56:08,644
I SAID I WANT TO BE LEFT ALONE

843
00:56:28,455 --> 00:56:31,000
YOU KILLED ME

844
00:56:34,795 --> 00:56:38,340
MY MOTHER-IN-LAW, AND THE CAFÉ OWNER

845
00:56:57,276 --> 00:57:00,571
YOU SLEPT WITH SEON, DIDN'T YOU?

846
00:57:04,366 --> 00:57:06,243
KIM GYUN

847
00:57:19,340 --> 00:57:20,341
Get in.

848
00:57:28,807 --> 00:57:30,225
Don't make a scene around here.

849
00:57:30,684 --> 00:57:31,936
Okay, so get in.

850
00:57:38,609 --> 00:57:40,903
<i>Legally speaking,</i>
<i>when you get divorced</i>

851
00:57:40,986 --> 00:57:43,030
<i>the one who had an affair</i>
<i>is the one at fault.</i>

852
00:57:43,280 --> 00:57:46,325
<i>That means the innocent one</i>
<i>is more advantageous</i>

853
00:57:46,408 --> 00:57:47,618
<i>when we divide the assets.</i>

854
00:57:47,701 --> 00:57:48,702
<i>I didn't have an affair</i>

855
00:57:49,495 --> 00:57:51,830
<i>but Seon did.</i>

856
00:57:53,791 --> 00:57:54,792
What is this?

857
00:57:56,085 --> 00:57:58,003
Su-jong is getting ready
to divorce you.

858
00:58:00,381 --> 00:58:01,382
What?

859
00:58:01,715 --> 00:58:03,634
You're about to be backstabbed.

860
00:58:06,887 --> 00:58:10,933
M&A REALTORS

861
00:58:26,532 --> 00:58:27,658
<i>What's going on?</i>

862
00:58:27,741 --> 00:58:29,159
Do you have trouble with your wife?

863
00:58:29,243 --> 00:58:30,995
Affairs, affairs.

864
00:58:31,078 --> 00:58:32,955
A wind of affairs is blowing.

865
00:58:38,168 --> 00:58:39,169
Hee-ju.

866
00:58:50,222 --> 00:58:51,223
Hee-ju.

867
00:58:59,523 --> 00:59:00,524
Hee-ju.

868
00:59:01,442 --> 00:59:03,068
Man, what time is it?

869
00:59:06,280 --> 00:59:07,281
Hee-ju.

870
00:59:08,282 --> 00:59:09,408
Get up.

871
00:59:10,701 --> 00:59:11,702
Hee-ju.

872
00:59:20,252 --> 00:59:21,253
What?

873
00:59:22,588 --> 00:59:24,590
SEON

874
00:59:43,942 --> 00:59:45,027
Hee-ju.

875
01:00:10,886 --> 01:00:13,806
MAD CONCRETE DREAMS

876
01:00:14,056 --> 01:00:16,183
<i>I really didn't do anything.</i>

877
01:00:16,266 --> 01:00:17,518
<i>Da-rae got accepted?</i>

878
01:00:17,601 --> 01:00:18,644
<i>You didn't know?</i>

879
01:00:18,727 --> 01:00:20,354
<i>She received</i>
<i>the acceptance e-mail last night.</i>

880
01:00:20,437 --> 01:00:23,273
We oppose forced development projects
that rob private property!

881
01:00:23,357 --> 01:00:24,441
- We oppose!
- We oppose!

882
01:00:24,525 --> 01:00:27,402
<i>Some are starting to catch on.</i>

883
01:00:27,486 --> 01:00:28,821
<i>Let's wrap this up quickly.</i>

884
01:00:29,113 --> 01:00:31,323
<i>I got a message from Da-rae.</i>
<i>What is this?</i>

885
01:00:31,406 --> 01:00:33,909
<i>This plan was put together</i>
<i>to take Se-yoon Building from me.</i>

886
01:00:34,159 --> 01:00:35,160
Da-rae.

887
01:00:35,244 --> 01:00:36,411
<i>Prepare yourself to divorce him.</i>

888
01:00:36,745 --> 01:00:38,580
<i>You already know</i>
<i>about the crimes Su-jong committed.</i>

889
01:00:38,664 --> 01:00:40,582
<i>You need clear evidence</i>
<i>to use against him.</i>

890
01:00:40,666 --> 01:00:41,667
<i>I'll give you a hand.</i>

891
01:00:54,805 --> 01:00:56,807
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
